South Africa’s main stock index gains 0.3% as of 9:58 a.m. in Johannesburg, as a weaker dollar boosts the prices of precious metals, with record bullion prices lifting gold producers to a fresh all time record, and higher platinum prices bolstering local producers. NOTE: Gold Surges to a Record With $2,000 an Ounce in Sight  Risk sentiment has been strengthened by optimism over the the upcoming US Federal Reserve meeting, which has drowned fears over simmering Sino-American tensions, as well as concerns of second waves of the coronavirus pandemic, with outbreaks from China to Spain serving as reminders of the difficulty in permanently stamping out the coronavirus. Investors will be looking to the Fed’s meeting for clues on what comes next for policy. © 2020 Bloomberg